"FINDINGS \u2014 completeness critique of combined research (verified against repo where contested)\n\n== 1. CONTRADICTIONS BETWEEN AGENTS ==\n\nC1. HL mainnet data vs testnet-lock (CRITICAL, unreconciled). hlSrc/sentimentSrc/newsSrc all build the plan on mainnet `https://api.hyperliquid.xyz/info` (predictedFundings, l2Book, listing-diff, leaderboard); execMap/docsMap state the spec forbids any mainnet field. VERIFIED: `tests/test_execution.py:274` asserts `not any(\"mainnet\" in name.lower() for name in vars(s))` \u2014 a `hyperliquid_mainnet_url` Settings field fails the suite as written. Also VERIFIED: `core/crypto_universe.py:290` hits only `settings.hyperliquid_testnet_url`, so today's listing/tradability plumbing is testnet-only while every recommended decision-data feed is mainnet. No agent proposed the reconciliation (read-only field named without \"mainnet\", e.g. `hl_info_url`, + CONTRACT \u00a717 amendment distinguishing read path from write path).\n\nC2. Egress geography. sentimentSrc presents evidence this box egresses via an AMS datacenter IP (CF-RAY *-AMS, Reddit hard-403); newsSrc twice asserts \"from this US machine / US IP\"; provMap/docsMap assume US-IP Binance 451 fallback to Bybit. These cannot all be true. Material because metricsRes's three must-have signals (taker field 9, topLongShortPositionRatio, /fapi/v1/fundingRate) are Binance-fapi-only and the Bybit fallback lacks taker volume and top-trader ratios entirely. NOBODY live-probed /fapi from this host \u2014 single most important unverified fact in the whole research set.\n\nC3. CoinGecko budget. Repo provider declares `rate_per_min = 10` (VERIFIED coingecko.py:43); sentimentSrc MEASURED 429 after ~5 calls/min keyless. The repo's own TokenBucket can exceed the real quota; metricsRes then proposes 3+ new CoinGecko calls (breadth, stablecoin caps, /coins/markets) on the same pool without addressing it. Fix: drop rate_per_min to 5 or require the free demo key path.\n\nC4. Funding source of truth. pipeMap scores funding from Binance/Bybit (8h baseline) and leverage_plan prices funding_cost from it; hlSrc proves HL funding is hourly and materially divergent (live example 0G: -0.0000916/1h HL vs +0.0000109/4h Binance) and calls the repo number \"WRONG for cost on an HL position\"; metricsRes builds funding z-history on Binance anyway. Agents agree on the problem but never designate the authoritative venue per use (signal = cross-venue OK; cost/carry in leverage_plan = must be HL).\n\nC5. CLAUDE.md memory files. docsMap says they don't exist and \"MCPenny project dir has no memory/\". VERIFIED: the MakeCrazyPenny path in CLAUDE.md does not exist (False); `C--Users-persi-Desktop-MCPenny\\memory` EXISTS but is EMPTY. docsMap wrong in letter, right in substance: the runbook docs the project says to \"read first\" are absent; CLAUDE.md links are stale.\n\nC6. orchRes truncation. Approach C cuts off mid-sentence; no cons for C, no comparison matrix, no final scheduling parameters. Its unverifiable specifics (Agent SDK credit June 15 2026 / $20-$100-$200 tiers, `claude/channel` capability, elicitation auto-approve hook) are presented as fact with no source-checking by any other agent.\n\nMinor consistencies confirmed: websocket-client 1.9.0 IS in the venv (verified, hlSrc correct); binance.py klines parse only rows 0-5 (verified, metricsRes \"field 9 discarded\" correct); PullPush staleness and CoinGecko /coins/list/new paywall internally consistent.\n\n== 2. CRITICAL MISSING PIECES FOR IMPLEMENTATION ==\n\nM1. Binance fapi reachability probe from this host + per-signal degradation matrix when chain falls to Bybit (no taker volume, no top-trader ratio \u2192 must-have metrics silently vanish).\nM2. HL read-provider design: capability names (hl_ctx/hl_funding/hl_l2book/...), CAPABILITIES tuple + chains + TTL edits in config.py, Settings field naming that passes the mainnet-attr test, CONTRACT amendment text. All agents assume it exists; none specified it.\nM3. LLM-output ingestion architecture. Sentiment/news agents produce model-classified polarity, but the engine convention is \"tools deterministic, never call a model\"; pipeMap's only merge point is `decide_from_scores(verdict=...)` at host level. Nobody decided: do haiku/sonnet outputs become scored dossier factors (violates AI-free engine) or host-fusion-only context (then they never affect conviction/sizing math)? This is the central unresolved design question of the swarm.\nM4. Conviction semantics recalibration: pipeMap flags the n_categories/4 divisor and >=2-category gate; metricsRes adds ~5 new categories without addressing it. No concrete plan (divisor growth, per-category caps, weight renormalization, re-tuned thresholds).\nM5. Journal/PnL concrete schema: execMap names every seam (cloid pass-through, _run chokepoint, user_fills_by_time, userFunding, JSONL helpers in servers/orchestration.py) but no agent wrote the record schema, file layout, episode-reconstruction algorithm, equity-snapshot cadence, or restart reconciliation. Kelly-calibration (metricsRes) depends on this and the dependency ordering is stated nowhere.\nM6. Concurrency control: orchRes B makes \"only host trades\" structural, but overlapping scheduled headless runs, multi-process rate budgets (provMap: N processes = N x full bucket), L2-cache races, and a single-instance lock/idempotency key are all unaddressed. No kill-switch, daily-loss cap, or max-open-positions implementation location named.\nM7. WS consumer placement: hlSrc verified 6 channels but no design for where an always-on WS loop lives relative to import-safe/no-network-at-import conventions, the sync registry, reconnection, or the 10-conn/IP cap shared across swarm processes.\nM8. Testnet executability of listing alpha: highest-touted edge (new-listing events) may be untradable \u2014 testnet universe is 208/230 and lags; nobody measured how often a fresh mainnet listing appears on testnet at all. Without this number the listing-watcher track's value is unknown.\nM9. Decision TTL/staleness fields (as_of/expiry on TradeDecision + pre-execution re-validation) \u2014 flagged as a gap by pipeMap, fixed by nobody.\nM10. No crypto backtest/validation path for the new weights (backtest.py is equity long/flat only); Santiment 30d-lagged data was floated for calibration but no harness design exists.\n\n== 3. TOP 5 PRIORITIES BY EDGE-PER-EFFORT ==\n\nP1. HL-native read provider (mainnet /info: metaAndAssetCtxs, predictedFundings, l2Book, fundingHistory) + OI-cap/maxLeverage/isDelisted tradability gates. Corrects an actually-wrong number (funding cost on HL positions), replaces N funding calls with 1, supplies impactPxs slippage and the listing-diff detector on the execution venue. Effort: one provider module + config entries following existing patterns, plus the naming/CONTRACT fix from C1. Highest edge density in the set.\nP2. Taker CVD/imbalance from kline field 9 (zero new HTTP calls \u2014 verified parser gap) + RVOL z-gate + Parkinson/YZ vol into risk sizing. Pure computation on already-fetched data; strongest academic backing; fills the engine's only structural blind spot (flow vs positioning). Gate on M1 (Binance reachability).\nP3. JSONL decision/trade journal + cloid threading + user_fills_by_time/userFunding wrappers + periodic equity snapshots. Prerequisite for the swarm's stated PnL-tracking goal, Kelly calibration, factor hit-rate telemetry, and restart reconciliation. All seams identified; FakeExchange already accepts cloid, JSON helpers already exist to lift.\nP4. Portfolio risk gate in paper_trade.py: BTC-beta-clustered correlated-notional cap, max same-direction positions, auto-downsize-to-fit, plus daily-loss kill-switch. Math fully specified by metricsRes; absence is the catastrophic failure mode for any concurrent swarm. Must land before any multi-position automation.\nP5. orchRes-B skeleton: swarm_goal/swarm_journal MCP tools + trade_swarm prompt + .claude/agents (haiku scout / sonnet news / opus TA, paper_* tools excluded) + scheduled headless loop WITH a single-instance lock. Everything verified-workable today on subscription billing; effort is mostly config/prompt files once P3's journal tools exist.\n\n(Deliberately below the line: listing-event watchers (pending M8), Arctic Shift/StockTwits sentiment pollers (lower evidence than derivatives-native signals, plus M3 unresolved), basis term structure/Hurst/VWAP/Coinbase-premium nice-to-haves.)\n\n== 4. SPEC-CONSTRAINT VIOLATIONS IN THE PROPOSALS ==\n\nV1. Testnet-lock: any `*mainnet*` Settings field fails tests/test_execution.py:274 and CONTRACT \u00a717.1 as written \u2014 hlSrc/sentimentSrc/newsSrc proposals all require the mainnet info URL. Needs deliberate naming (no \"mainnet\" substring) + CONTRACT amendment scoping the invariant to the signed write path; otherwise every HL-data proposal is a violation.\nV2. AI-free engine: feeding haiku/sonnet classifications into score_crypto_evidence or any MCP tool calling a model breaks \"tools are deterministic and never call a model\" and pure-scoring conventions. Must enter via host verdict merge or stay out of the engine (see M3).\nV3. Keyless-first: CryptoPanic, CoinMarketCal, LunarCrush, CoinGecko demo key are acceptable only as optional keyed providers using the MissingApiKey silent-skip contract; orchRes approach A's FastMCP sampling_handler fallback requires an Anthropic API key \u2014 correctly rejected, but any dormant ctx.sample code must stay lazily imported (import-safe).\nV4. ASCII: Upbit titles are Korean; 4chan/Reddit bodies are arbitrary Unicode. Any tool/CLI output echoing raw titles violates the strict-ASCII rule \u2014 extract Latin tickers via regex and strip/sanitize everything else before surfacing.\nV5. Import-safe/offline tests: an always-on WS client or poller must not connect at import or break test_imports; pollers need monkeypatch seams like get_registry/_build_clients. Unofficial endpoints (Binance bapi CMS, Upbit api-manager, stats-data leaderboard, CMC data-api) must raise on shape change (breaker-counted) and be declared best-effort, never hard dependencies.\nV6. Live-by-default + scheduled headless runs + auto-approved elicitation = unattended order placement in a loop with no kill-switch; not a literal spec breach (testnet only) but removes the only human gate noted in \u00a717.1 \u2014 require the P4 risk gate and an off-switch env flag before enabling the scheduler.\nV7. Venue-exact margin: leverage.py flat mmr=0.005 ignores HL marginTableId tiers while proposals size real testnet margin from it \u2014 correctness gap to fix alongside P1 (pipeMap flagged; no proposal addresses it)."